title: Minimal Reliance on Coal for Electricity
description: In 2021, Latvia's electricity production from coal sources was nearly negligible at 0.00017% of the total, showcasing a strong shift towards cleaner energy sources.

title: Low Prevalence of Underweight in Children
description: As of 2021, only 0.3% of children under five in Latvia were underweight, indicating effective nutritional and health policies.

title: Minimal Stunting in Children
description: In 2021, Latvia reported a stunting prevalence of just 0.5% among children under five, reflecting positive child health outcomes.

title: Balanced Female Age Distribution
description: In 2023, females aged 25-29 made up 4.23% of the female population, suggesting a balanced age distribution within the demographic.
